'''Trial graphics''' are images that have been designed by expert [[graphic artist]]s for use in [[legal trial]]s and procedures. Graphs and other images can be created to use as [[evidence|evidential]] support in a [[court of law]] by utilizing current [[graphic design]] technology.

Effective [[jury]] presentations are a key point to creating a strong legal case. High quality legal graphics are a relatively new tool that can be utilized by [[lawyer]]s looking to add clear forms of analytic data or other designed images for jury review.<ref>[http://www.trialgraphix.com/SiteAssets/file/Articles/TrendsStatsBestPractices_Douglas_Skoke.pdf Best Practices for Using Graphic Design in Trial.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121070319/http://www.trialgraphix.com/SiteAssets/file/Articles/trendsstatsbestpractices_douglas_skoke.pdf |date=2013-01-21 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.trialgraphix.com/SiteAssets/file/Articles/thejuryexpert-leslieellis-september-26-2011.pdf Utilize a Jury Expert to ensure victory at trial.]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref>

